'''Explanation:'''

A series of experiments were conducted by Kuubowokyuu over 3 months, to study how choosing different formations (''Line Ahead, Double Line, Echelon, Line Abreast'') will affect your fleet's night battle performances. Namely:
*I - [http://kancolle.wikia.com/wiki/User_blog:Homuhomu123/How_Formation_Affects_Night_Battle_Performances_(by_Kuubowokyuu)#I_-_Accuracy_.26_Evasion_of_Your_Fleet Accuracy and evasion of your fleet.]
*II - [http://kancolle.wikia.com/wiki/User_blog:Homuhomu123/How_Formation_Affects_Night_Battle_Performances_(by_Kuubowokyuu)#Ii_-_DA_Chance_of_Your_Fleet_.26_CI_Chance_of_the_Enemies DA chance of your fleet.& CI chance of the enemies.]

The attacking ships & the targets are recorded accordingly in chart format.''' As the author mentioned, the sample sizes are small (50~300+) '''thus please be cautious when drawing conclusions from the data below.''' '''Note that larger samples usually give more accurate results. If you would like to see the exact sample sizes for each experiment, you may go to the Appendix section attached below.

'''<u>Test ship condition</u>
'''
*Test map: 5-3-1
*Morale are kept at 49.
*Test ships are beyond moderate damage, otherwise data were not recorded.
*Each consecutive cut-in or double attack is recorded separately. (i.e. they're regarded as 2 attacks rather than 1)
*Scratches (1%~14% of the enemy's current HP) are counted as miss.
'''<u>Enemy condition</u>
'''
*Always line ahead.
'''<u>Test ships & equipment</u>
'''
*Yuudachi K2 & Hibiki K2:  Lv99,  evasion stat = 89,  10cm HA x2
*Kitakami K2 & Ooi K2:      Lv99,  evasion stat = 83,  20.3cm x2 + mini-sub
*''Since they're using DA setup for night battle, they'll be doing DA for most fo the time, with a few single attacks.''





